The Monstera Deliciosa is a tropical plant also known as the Swiss Cheese plant, Split-Leaf Philodendron, or Mexican Breadfruit, among many other names. Its name comes from a Latin word meaning “abnormal” because of its unique, odd-looking, and perforated leaves that are often punched through with holes. This unique and vibrant houseplant is best for living and dining room spaces as it makes for a very interesting conversational piece.
